# Cortex CODEOWNERS — security-invariant protection.
#
# GitHub / Gitea / Gerrit read this file and require the listed
# reviewer(s) to approve any PR that touches the matching paths.
# The point is not "one maintainer bottlenecks all work" — the point
# is that relaxing a security invariant should never happen silently.
#
# Whoever is the acting maintainer at the time the repo is deployed
# commercially should replace @tmaloziec with their handle + any
# co-owners. Before then this file mostly documents intent.

# Default: any change in the repo needs a maintainer look.
*           @tmaloziec

# The security invariants themselves. Relaxing a rule, adding a new
# KIND, changing the untrusted-container contract, widening an
# allow-list — all must go through a reviewer who understands why
# the invariant exists.
/security/                  @tmaloziec
/tests/test_invariants.py   @tmaloziec
/tests/test_policy.py       @tmaloziec
/policy.py                  @tmaloziec
/SECURITY.md                @tmaloziec

# R14/#5: protect CI configuration + the CODEOWNERS file itself.
# Otherwise a PR could disable the guards or drop the ownership rule
# in the same diff.
/.github/                   @tmaloziec
/CODEOWNERS                 @tmaloziec
/conftest.py                @tmaloziec
/run.sh                     @tmaloziec

# Dependency pins (CVE-relevant).
/requirements.txt           @tmaloziec

# Commercial licensing surface — change intent, not code style.
/LICENSE                    @tmaloziec
/LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md      @tmaloziec
/CLA.md                     @tmaloziec
